  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dad\u0dcf\u0db4\u0dbd\u0dca,\u0dbd\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dd6\u0dab \u0dc3\u0dc4 \u0db4\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dca\u0db4\u0dd4 \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0dba\u0dc5\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0dc4\u0dad\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The prices of potato, lokuluna and dal are down again",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to market sources, the prices of several essential consumer goods including potatoes, onions and lentils have fallen.",
        "It was seen that the retail price of a kilo of domestically imported potatoes in Petaling Jaya has dropped to 180 rupees, and the price of a kilo of large onions has dropped to 150 rupees.",
        "Domestic potato prices have also come down to Rs 380. At Narahenpita Economic Center, the price of a kilo of imported potatoes will be reduced to 220 rupees. The price of imported potatoes was around 230-240 rupees two weeks ago.",
        "The price of a kilo of big onion has dropped to 150 rupees, while it remained at 170 rupees in Narahenpita Economic Centre.",
        "In Lanka Sathosa stores, onions were sold as 165 kilos. The price of big onion used to be between 220-240 rupees per kilo. Imported potatoes are not available in most supermarkets and they only have local potatoes. Its price per kilo was displayed as 560 rupees.",
        "Lentil prices have also come down significantly. Currently, dal is between 460 and 480 rupees per kg. It was seen as 485 rupees in Lanka Satho.",
        "Dry chillies were sold at 1600 rupees per kg in Petat Kota while it was 1640 rupees in Narahenpita economic center.",
        "The price of white sugar was between 300 and 305 rupees per kilo in the economic centers of Petaling Jaya and Narahenpita. Lanka Sathose white sugar can be bought for 298 rupees per kg. But sugar prices in supermarkets are still between 356 and 359 rupees per kilo."
      ],
